# API Documentation

# Friends Like These: Campus Key Edition

---

# Overview

This document describes the APIs and external services used by the Friends Like These: Campus Key Edition application.

The application integrates with several cloud-based services to provide real-time functionality without requiring a traditional backend server.

Current integrations include:

- Firebase Realtime Database
- Google Forms
- Google Sheets
- QR Code Generation

---

# API Architecture

```
Browser

↓

JavaScript Application

↓

Firebase Realtime Database

↓

Google Forms

↓

Google Sheets
```

---

# External APIs

## Firebase Realtime Database

### Purpose

Stores and synchronises application data in real time.

### Responsibilities

- Store teams
- Store scores
- Store event information
- Synchronise changes
- Notify connected clients

---

### Base URL

```
https://<project-id>.firebaseio.com/
```

---

### Data Structure

```
teams/

event/

scores/

settings/
```

---

## Retrieve Teams

### Method

```
GET
```

### Endpoint

```
/teams.json
```

### Description

Retrieves all registered teams.

---

### Example Response

```json
{
  "team001": {
    "teamName": "Dominant FC",
    "score": 80
  },

  "team002": {
    "teamName": "The Winners",
    "score": 65
  }
}
```

---

## Create Team

### Method

```
POST
```

### Endpoint

```
/teams.json
```

### Description

Creates a new team.

---

### Request Example

```json
{
    "teamName":"Dominant FC",
    "score":0
}
```

---

### Response

```json
{
    "name":"team001"
}
```

---

## Update Team Score

### Method

```
PATCH
```

### Endpoint

```
/teams/{teamId}.json
```

---

### Example Request

```json
{
    "score":120
}
```

---

### Example Response

```json
{
    "score":120
}
```

---

## Delete Team

### Method

```
DELETE
```

### Endpoint

```
/teams/{teamId}.json
```

---

### Description

Deletes the selected team.

---

# Google Forms

## Purpose

Collect participant registrations.

Participants complete an online registration form.

The responses are automatically stored inside Google Sheets.

---

### Registration Workflow

```
Participant

↓

Google Form

↓

Google Sheets

↓

Application
```

---

# Google Sheets API

## Purpose

Imports registration data submitted through Google Forms.

---

### Responsibilities

- Read spreadsheet
- Retrieve participant data
- Convert rows into Team objects

---

### API Endpoint

```
https://sheets.googleapis.com/v4/spreadsheets/{spreadsheetId}/values/{range}
```

---

### Method

```
GET
```

---

### Example Response

```json
{
 "values":[
   [
      "Dominant FC",
      "Alice",
      "John"
   ]
 ]
}
```

---

# QR Code Integration

